<h4>Sharing Activities</h4>
<p>
    Park:Learn lets users launch your shared activities in two ways: scanning QR Codes and typing share codes into the app. The easiest way to share your activity is by using the Park:Learn website. When logged into the site, go to the "My Activities" page in the top menu (or side drawer if on mobile).
    Here you will see a list of all of your uploaded activities. Clicking an activity will present you with its share page, featuring a QR code and share code. Clicking the QR code will give you a larger version for printing. Alternatively, you can view your activities' share codes by tapping them
    in the 'My Activities' tab.
</p>

<p>If the user already has Park:Learn installed, they can start the activity in a few ways:</p>
<ul class="bullet">
    <li>The <i class="material-icons">search</i> search icon at the top of the app's screen lets users enter a given share code and immediately open the matching activity.</li>
    <li>The scan icon at the top of the app's screen lets users scan a QR Code and immediately open the matching activity.</li>
    <li>Scanning the QR Code in a separate app will give the user the choice of opening the activity in Park:Learn or viewing the share page in their web browser.</li>
    <li>If you visit an activity's share page on a device supported by Park:Learn, there will be a button to launch your activity directly in the app.</li>
</ul>

<p>If the user doesn't have Park:Learn installed, they can use another app to scan the QR Code. This will bring them to the activity's share page, from which they can install the app.</p>